node.accessibility_caption: Photo by National Park Geek® in Katmai National Park & Preserve with @chasedekkerphotography, @alaska.geographic, and @katmainpp. May be an image of animal and nature.

node.text:
We agree, sometimes you just have to stop and take it all in. 
••••
Thanks to Chase  @chasedekkerphotography for sharing the beauty of the moment. 
•
I think it’s about time I finally started sharing some photos from the past few months!

While I have many more images showing more interesting wildlife behavior, this shot of a coastal brown bear cub just makes me smile looking at it. I remember shooting this cub and the rest of his family one evening along the Alaskan Peninsula as they mowed down some sedge grass with 30 other bears around. At one point, this little cub decided he needed a break and just sat down scanning his surroundings. I don’t ever want to anthropomorphize wildlife actions, but it just seemed like he was taking it all in for a brief minute.
